-- Tokyo Stock Exchange to Set Up International Bond Market, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2010-11-09T17:21:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/tokyo-stock-exchange-to-set-up-international-bond-market-nikkei-reports.html
The Tokyo Stock Exchange will
introduce an international corporate bond market next year to be
operated by Tokyo AIM, a venture with the London Stock Exchange,
Nikkei English News reported.  The market will let issuers offer debt in a range of
currencies, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  